# Issue Guardrails for Consistency

This file defines strict guardrails to ensure consistent issue generation across any AI model.

---

## 1. FORMAT GUARDRAILS (EXACT TEMPLATE STRUCTURE)

**RULE: Every issue file MUST contain these sections in THIS EXACT ORDER:**

```markdown
1. # [Issue Title]                          ← H1 heading, actual title (NOT "## Title")
2. ---
3. ## Summary
4. ---
5. ## Learning goals
6. ---
7. ## Requirements / Acceptance criteria
8. ---
9. ## Step-by-step guide
10. ---
11. ## Time estimate
12. ---
13. ## Constraints
14. ---
15. ## Dependencies
16. ---
17. ## Definition of Done
18. ---
19. ## Raise PR
```

**VIOLATIONS (Will cause INVALID issue):**
- ⛔ Missing ANY section
- ⛔ Sections in different order
- ⛔ Adding extra sections
- ⛔ Using `## Title` heading instead of `# Actual Title`

**EXCEPTION:** Issue #01 (Project Setup) uses README format only

